(102, 1, '2022-10-03 21:18:17', '2022-10-03 21:18:17', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The story is balanced between a narrative in present day&nbsp;New York City&nbsp;and flashbacks starting from Addie\'s childhood in France to her experiences traveling the world and witnessing major historical events. It begins in the early 1700s, following Addie as a young woman burdened by forced marriage&nbsp;and praying to the gods for her freedom. She accidentally catches the attention of a god of the night, who she would later name&nbsp;Luc, who promises her the time she wants with the caveat being nobody will ever remember her after one encounter. Over time she subtly influences many people, making marks in history and inspiring the creation of songs and art about her. Luc visits her every year after they make their deal, asking for her soul, but she refuses every time. The pair develop a&nbsp;relationship&nbsp;over time that carries on for about two decades. It ends abruptly when Luc asks again for her to surrender her soul, as Addie believes their relationship was just a gambit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://jlenz19.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/review/\">Check out the reviews!</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'the Invisible Life of Addie LaRue', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-invisible-life-of-addie-larue', '', '', '2022-10-05 15:05:41', '2022-10-05 15:05:41', '', 0, 'https://jlenz19.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=book&#038;p=102', 0, 'book', '', 0),
