(104, 1, '2022-10-03 21:26:21', '2022-10-03 21:26:21', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It has been four months since a mysterious obsidian stone fell into Kell\'s possession. Four months since his path crossed with Delilah Bard. Four months since Prince Rhy was wounded, and since the nefarious Dane twins of White London fell, and four months since the stone was cast with Holland\'s dying body through the rift--back into Black London.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, restless after having given up his smuggling habit, Kell is visited by dreams of ominous magical events, waking only to think of Lila, who disappeared from the docks as she always meant to do. As Red London finalizes preparations for the Element Games--an extravagant international competition of magic meant to entertain and keep healthy the ties between neighboring countries--a certain pirate ship draws closer, carrying old friends back into port.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://jlenz19.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/review/\">Check out the reviews!</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'A Gathering of Shadows', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-gathering-of-shadows', '', '', '2022-10-05 15:04:40', '2022-10-05 15:04:40', '', 0, 'https://jlenz19.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=book&#038;p=104', 0, 'book', '', 0),
